Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff-brown. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Epikrates A parallel in Toronto is from same die. Oxford, Ashmolean Museum 1888.199i is from a different die. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0551)
